<font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="4" color="#990000"><b>What else to read</b></font><p>
<font face="Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif" size="2">For an overview of the movement against the Vietnam War, see Fred Halstead's <i><a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/redirect.html?ie=UTF8&amp;location=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FParticipants-Account-Movement-Against-Vietnam%2Fdp%2FB000H2GLPO%2Fsr%3D8-2%2Fqid%3D1168998599%3Fie%3DUTF8%26amp%3Bs%3Dbooks&amp;tag=socialistwork-20&amp;linkCode=ur2" target="_blank">Out Now! A Participant's Account of the Movement in the United States Against the Vietnam War</a>. </i>Kirkpatrick Sale's <i><a href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/redirect.html?ie=UTF8&amp;location=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.amazon.com%2FSDS-Kirkpatrick-Sale%2Fdp%2F0394719654%2Fsr%3D1-1%2Fqid%3D1168998655%3Fie%3DUTF8%26amp%3Bs%3Dbooks&amp;tag=socialistwork-20&amp;linkCode=ur2&amp;camp=1789&amp;creati" target="_blank">SDS</a> </i>also provides a useful view of the movement.<p>
Joel Geier's article <a href="http://www.isreview.org/issues/09/soldiers_revolt.shtml" target="_blank">"Vietnam: The Soldiers' Revolt"</a> is an important document of the GI resistance, published in the <i><a href="http://www.isreview.org" target="_blank">International Socialist Review</a>.</i> Also online at the <i>ISR</i> Web site is Joe Allen's <a href="http://www.isreview.org/issues/29/vietnam.shtml" target="_blank">three-part history of the Vietnam War</a>.
